        "h1": null,
        "style": "light",
        "decorator": "none",
        "content": "<h3>When choosing the right ecommerce platform for your enterprise business, you will not have the myriad of solutions available to small and midsize businesses &ndash; you will want to focus on evaluating a few platforms, including SAP Hybris and it&#39;s competitors: Salesforce Commerce Cloud, Shopify, Magento and Virto Commerce. As B2B ecommerce experts, we get a lot of questions from customers trying to evaluate SAP Hybris vs Magento vs other B2B ecommerce platforms. We will look at SAP Hybris and one of it&#39;s main alternatives, Magento, as well as Virto Commerce &ndash; a rapidly growing B2B ecommerce platform utilized by Heineken, Volvo, Rainbow Sandals and a variety of enterprise businesses.</h3>\n\n<p>SAP Commerce Cloud (recently rebranded from SAP Hybris) is one of the most well-known cloud ecommerce platforms available. Around since the 1990s, the platform helped usher in the big dotcom boom of the early 2000s.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nSince its inception, it has evolved into a highly agile ecommerce platform for both B2B and B2C selling, with modules and accelerators that have been developed for specific industries like grocery, education, insurance and apparel.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nIn addition to these plug and use modules that can customize the platform for specific industries, it can also be integrated with other SAP Cloud platforms for a seamless ecommerce process from the front to back ends.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nSAP Commerce Cloud can be used by non-tech savvy ecommerce store owners, as it comes with many ready-to-use templates for common ecommerce functions, including promotions. It is highly customizable, integrates well with other services and is scalable to handle large shopping days.&nbsp;</p>\n",
