        "type": "text",
        "name": "Text",
        "title": "Why consider alternatives to SAP (Hybris) Commerce Cloud?Â ",
        "h1": null,
        "style": "light",
        "decorator": "none",
        "content": "<p>As good as SAP Commerce Cloud is, the platform does have some drawbacks. Most notably, since it uses some older functionality, it could stand for an update to its Content Management System and some of the aforementioned modules. While you don&#39;t need to be tech savvy to use the platform, those who are will be able to get better use out of it.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nUnlike platforms that have the value of being open source, SAP Hybris is a closed platform. It&#39;s not flexible and easy to customize &ndash; greatly limiting your business. With the rapid pace of ecommerce change, using a platform that doesn&#39;t offer agility and extensibility could prove to be an expensive mistake in the long run, as replatforming or changing your SAP Commerce Cloud solution is quite pricey and time consuming.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nThe out-of-the-box promotion templates are useful, but if you can&#39;t find one that fits your exact needs, customizing them will require more advanced technical knowledge.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nIf you are a small operation and you don&#39;t have a dedicated IT team, SAP Commerce Cloud could pose a problem since it doesn&#39;t have the comprehensive support and guidance that other platforms on the market offer.&nbsp;</p>\n",
